Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.54,0:00:05.40,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Nureha!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.51,0:00:06.94,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Nureha!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.58,0:00:09.53,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Londark, anything to report?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.83,0:00:11.56,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.56,0:00:14.03,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The princess does what she pleases, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.03,0:00:16.21,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Does Mizufa intend to search for her?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.21,0:00:18.78,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell you what Mizufa had to say...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.01,0:00:22.88,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,We're in the middle of Operation Red Night.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.88,0:00:26.41,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,And if Miss Nureha left of her own free will,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.41,0:00:28.54,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,it's none of our business.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.11,0:00:31.41,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Is that sarcasm, Londark?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.41,0:00:34.55,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The princess is the leader of Plant Hwyaden!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.76,0:00:40.34,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Nureha...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.00,0:00:45.24,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,If you were going home, \Nyou should have taken me, Loreil.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.17,0:00:51.31,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,West?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.32,0:02:30.12,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Again...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.63,0:02:32.25,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,The Odyssey Knights, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.51,0:02:36.95,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Around here, they aren't such an unusual sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.95,0:02:38.26,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.60,0:02:41.01,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,The People of the Land welcome them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.35,0:02:46.02,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,They risk their lives fighting to \Nprotect the villages and towns.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.02,0:02:51.76,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,They do seem a bit tense, \Nbut they're so cool and disciplined.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.27,0:02:53.54,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.54,0:02:55.63,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,They do seem like they'd be \Nhandy to have around...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.63,0:02:56.90,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like that thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.32,0:02:59.19,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,It just doesn't feel right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.62,0:03:00.78,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Me, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.35,0:03:02.76,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't say why.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.57,0:03:09.54,Title,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1531,1)}When the Concert Ends
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.13,0:03:07.77,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,When the Concert Ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.40,0:03:12.92,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Let's eat!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.77,0:03:17.28,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,How is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.87,0:03:20.17,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't gotten any better at it...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.52,0:03:23.06,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true. It's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.06,0:03:24.45,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,It's perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.45,0:03:26.51,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,You're getting better and better at cooking.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.74,0:03:29.13,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,And under this star-filled sky...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.13,0:03:30.64,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It's a fantastic dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.18,0:03:33.52,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,You're all so close.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.52,0:03:35.19,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Because we're friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.19,0:03:36.90,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, we're friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.90,0:03:39.53,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't mind my asking,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.53,0:03:43.16,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,why are you headed to the Redstone Mountains?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.52,0:03:45.41,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to hunt a wyvern.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.70,0:03:48.48,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,We need it for the materials for a magic bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.93,0:03:50.48,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.12,0:03:54.65,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,We're almost to the town of Safil, aren't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.65,0:03:56.01,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.01,0:03:57.88,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Have you ever been there, Dariella?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.22,0:04:01.13,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,It's on my way home, so I've \Nbeen there a few times.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.69,0:04:04.93,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Once we get there, I'd like to hold a concert!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.27,0:04:06.67,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,A concert?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.67,0:04:07.93,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.93,0:04:11.17,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, Roe 2 hasn't seen one, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.17,0:04:14.16,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Isuzu is a bard.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.15,0:04:17.32,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm still not much more than an amateur.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.32,0:04:21.03,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Wherever we go, she plays all \Nkinds of different songs.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.03,0:04:22.70,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Music?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.44,0:04:30.20,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Back at Blume Hall in Akihabara, \NI was called a rock 'n' roller!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.20,0:04:32.08,Default,Ro,0000,0000,0000,,A rock 'n' roller?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.08,0:04:35.96,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Um, in other words, they think she's cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.25,0:04:37.69,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.69,0:04:38.96,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,That's leaving too much out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.26,0:04:42.21,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,You play music, though. That's interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.21,0:04:44.08,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,It's kind of wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.19,0:04:50.62,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, when we get to Safil, we'll do one!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.62,0:04:52.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.37,0:04:57.00,Location,I,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(341,1)\an9}The Town of Safil\N{\fs18}Japan Server\NSouth Fuji Area\NCity/ Monsters Present\NPVP Permitted\NSkill Use Permitted\NEntry Restrictions/ None\NExit Restrictions/ None
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.36,0:04:59.40,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,I can hear a song of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.40,0:05:03.61,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,Let me be closer to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.61,0:05:11.41,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,I'll change color and shape to protect you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.41,0:05:15.64,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,I can hear a song of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.64,0:05:19.54,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,If I can keep looking at you,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.54,0:05:26.55,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,even these blurred days will feel precious to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.55,0:05:35.17,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,Always... Always...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.19,0:05:37.73,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.08,0:05:39.73,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Want another song?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.06,0:05:43.15,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, here we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.85,0:05:50.79,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,That was fun...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.79,0:05:52.49,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm full.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.94,0:05:56.60,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Isuzu, are you sure \Nyou didn't eat too much?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.60,0:05:58.35,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't help it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.35,0:05:59.41,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.04,0:06:04.25,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,People of the Land kept buying me food.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.55,0:06:06.78,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Still, it was a good concert today.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.19,0:06:08.75,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Another good concert, you mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.75,0:06:10.75,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Another good one, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.10,0:06:16.77,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Isuzu, you really do \Nlove instruments, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.13,0:06:18.32,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I love them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.32,0:06:21.90,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,But you still keep saying you're not \Nmuch more than an amateur?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.71,0:06:23.73,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.73,0:06:26.28,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like I'm trying to be humble or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.39,0:06:33.02,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I may have said this before, \Nbut my dad was a pro musician.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.02,0:06:34.09,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.09,0:06:38.46,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Then the reason you're so good is due to \Nyour father's blood and your training.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.46,0:06:40.71,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come on, that's a bit of a stretch.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.13,0:06:44.07,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,My dad was a really free spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.07,0:06:45.79,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,He was a rock 'n' roller.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.79,0:06:47.39,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,He was so cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.39,0:06:51.26,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,He had long hair that flowed in the \Nwind, and this leather jacket.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.26,0:06:53.05,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,His legs were so thin.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.86,0:06:57.93,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,And he loved to brag to me, his daughter...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.27,0:07:01.13,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Stories about the things he did \Nwhen he was young, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.13,0:07:03.60,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,He worked at a part-time job \Nto buy this lousy old car,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.60,0:07:06.62,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,and he put all his instruments \Nin it and went touring.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.62,0:07:08.49,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,He said he went from Tokyo all around the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.88,0:07:10.32,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Like us?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.32,0:07:12.12,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.64,0:07:14.48,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,He sounds like a wonderful father.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.48,0:07:15.51,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.51,0:07:19.75,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,He was a little weird, but he was my hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.32,0:07:22.58,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,He even made his major debut!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.49,0:07:25.11,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Major debut?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.11,0:07:27.69,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,A major record company streamed his music.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.95,0:07:33.10,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, in other words... He got really famous.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.10,0:07:36.84,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,So famous you could hear his band's \Nsongs all around the town.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.84,0:07:38.36,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,That's amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.84,0:07:44.10,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,But you know, in my world, there are \Na lot of amazing people like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.51,0:07:47.60,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Every year, over a hundred people \Nmake their major debuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.60,0:07:50.81,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,But most of them don't last long...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.06,0:07:57.13,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Only a handful keep selling \Nlong after their debut.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.58,0:08:00.37,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,And my dad wasn't one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.03,0:08:02.84,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Did he quit?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.84,0:08:06.31,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,No, he loved music, so he couldn't quit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.80,0:08:10.01,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,So he became a studio musician.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.19,0:08:13.51,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,That's, well... How should I describe it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.51,0:08:16.91,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I know. He became a super-pro instrument player.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.91,0:08:19.52,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,He helps out many different \Npeople with their music.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.86,0:08:23.24,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Then you'll make your major debut, won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.24,0:08:24.33,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.33,0:08:26.29,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,A major debut is something professionals do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.29,0:08:28.81,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,You play, and it makes everyone happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.81,0:08:30.00,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't that make you a pro?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.00,0:08:31.19,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,No, it doesn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.81,0:08:40.29,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry... I'm not like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.57,0:08:43.09,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I like the lute, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.09,0:08:44.18,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I love it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.18,0:08:45.70,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,And I love singing, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.55,0:08:50.55,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,But... I don't have any talent.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.85,0:08:56.43,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,My dad would always say that \Nbecoming a pro was really hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.00,0:08:59.54,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,You're expected to have natural talent.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.54,0:09:02.22,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you do, you have to \Nwork as hard as you can,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.22,0:09:04.71,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,and only then can you see the starting line.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.71,0:09:05.73,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.73,0:09:08.74,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,So I'm happy just doing it because I like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.74,0:09:10.94,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,And it makes everyone happy, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.20,0:09:14.45,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I also love your songs, Miss Isuzu.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.62,0:09:18.09,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,You're so nice, Rudy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.09,0:09:20.83,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I'm nothing special at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.02,0:09:22.67,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,That isn't true.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.67,0:09:26.89,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,We all look forward to hearing your songs.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.89,0:09:29.21,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,To hearing a forty-two we don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.42,0:09:32.21,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Forty-two?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.21,0:09:36.44,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes, it seems like we're not \Nreally understanding each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.44,0:09:37.49,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.84,0:09:39.22,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,So that's how it sounds to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.97,0:09:42.86,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's happened to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.86,0:09:44.17,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,You, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.17,0:09:48.94,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,A while back, I asked for fish paste at \Na store, and they gave me flour paste.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.94,0:09:50.45,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.45,0:09:52.46,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably because of that...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.46,0:09:53.73,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,That?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.73,0:09:55.24,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,The auto-translator.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.24,0:09:59.24,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, the one that lets you \Ntalk with foreign players.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.24,0:10:00.15,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.15,0:10:02.77,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,It seems like the languages of adventurers
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.77,0:10:05.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and People of the Land are actually a bit different.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.20,0:10:10.43,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Normally, thanks to the auto-translator, \Nwe can talk to each other...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.43,0:10:11.75,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.75,0:10:16.76,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes, there are things the system \Ncan't handle, and it causes errors.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.08,0:10:18.44,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.44,0:10:21.51,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Then that's why we don't \Nalways understand each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.78,0:10:23.16,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Let me see...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.16,0:10:26.02,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,If I say, "seven colors," what do you think of?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.62,0:10:27.77,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,A rainbow?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.06,0:10:32.93,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. If I say, "seven colors," in People of \Nthe Land's language, it means a rainbow.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.28,0:10:35.30,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Then what's "forty-two"?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.71,0:10:36.95,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Music.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.46,0:10:38.28,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.04,0:10:44.03,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,To us, the People of the Land, \N"music" only encompasses forty-two songs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.18,0:10:50.54,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,God only gave our ancestors \Nthose forty-two songs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.05,0:10:53.77,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,And we can't make new ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.11,0:10:57.91,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,A leftover from when it was a game?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.57,0:11:01.72,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,That's the only music we have.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.26,0:11:04.10,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Since we were born, that's how it's always been.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.56,0:11:08.18,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,We thought that was normal, and went our \Nwhole lives without thinking about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.74,0:11:11.69,Default - italics,I,0000,0000,0000,,I never considered that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.06,0:11:18.69,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,So, Isuzu, we really love the songs \Nyou sing and the music you play.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.86,0:11:23.81,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember the inns \Nand pubs before we left?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.41,0:11:29.20,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,You just played a simple song, \Nand everyone was so happy, they cried.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.35,0:11:32.12,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,They were really happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.59,0:11:35.79,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Bright, upbeat songs that they'd never heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.24,0:11:38.38,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Songs that made them want to dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.64,0:11:41.63,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Or songs that made them want to \Nbe with someone they cared for.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.24,0:11:44.87,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,We'd never heard anything like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.41,0:11:49.50,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,And you brought them to us.\NThat made you a hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.18,0:11:52.36,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Rudy...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.17,0:11:56.23,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think Isuzu will become a pro?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.23,0:11:58.68,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I think she wants to, honestly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.68,0:12:03.33,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,It must be nice to have something \Nyou're better at than anyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.05,0:12:05.57,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.57,0:12:09.82,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,I'm jealous of how she can sing and \Nplay an instrument like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.82,0:12:12.49,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not really good at anything I try.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.49,0:12:16.00,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Have you ever thought about your future, Serara?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.00,0:12:18.81,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,You mean if we get back to our world?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.81,0:12:20.10,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, if we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.10,0:12:21.63,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,No, even if we don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.63,0:12:23.24,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Like, what you want to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.24,0:12:25.52,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.52,0:12:27.30,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't really clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.30,0:12:28.67,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.67,0:12:31.67,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,You seem like you've really thought about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.54,0:12:33.99,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.99,0:12:36.06,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I know who I'd want to be like...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.84,0:12:38.57,Default - italics,M,0000,0000,0000,,I want to be like Shiroe.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.03,0:12:42.15,Default - italics,M,0000,0000,0000,,But what does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.15,0:12:44.54,Default - italics,M,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't his job, I know that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.54,0:12:48.58,Default - italics,M,0000,0000,0000,,And no one could replace him, anyway...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.58,0:12:51.47,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,I just don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.47,0:12:52.58,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Minori?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.42,0:12:58.38,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Did you notice that more and more young \NPeople of the Land are coming to Akihabara?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.38,0:12:59.21,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.47,0:13:02.58,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,They're all coming because they \Nhave dreams for their future.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.58,0:13:05.95,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Blacksmiths, tailors, chefs, musicians...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.95,0:13:07.46,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,A lot of others, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.83,0:13:10.26,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Just a few months in Akihabara \Nwill teach you skills
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.26,0:13:13.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you couldn't learn in a lifetime anywhere else.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.43,0:13:16.28,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,You can be who you want to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.25,0:13:18.73,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Like you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.73,0:13:20.50,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.50,0:13:22.29,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I became an adventurer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.80,0:13:24.79,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,They also have something they want to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.47,0:13:28.99,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,We get together to talk about that stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.87,0:13:34.79,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I occasionally run off.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.69,0:13:39.92,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It's sometimes hard for People of \Nthe Land to live in Akihabara.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.92,0:13:41.55,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,But it's lucky, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.99,0:13:44.35,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Every day, something happens there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.04,0:13:49.10,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,What you couldn't do yesterday \Nmay be possible today.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.79,0:13:52.99,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Tomorrow will be different from today...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.52,0:13:58.19,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,And your songs are one of the wonderful \Nthings to be found there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.10,0:14:04.94,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,The People of the Land are all thinking \Nabout their futures, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.52,0:14:07.20,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not even...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.70,0:14:14.61,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I feel embarrassed for irresponsibly \Nsinging about love and life...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.61,0:14:16.93,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,No, Miss Isuzu, that isn't—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.93,0:14:18.71,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Rudy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.67,0:14:21.96,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,You can go back to your room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.88,0:14:28.00,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.74,0:14:50.72,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so pathetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.82,0:15:01.90,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, there was \Na river next to Choushi, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.90,0:15:04.42,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Why is that, again? Umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.85,0:15:07.72,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Settling near a river gives a town plenty of water,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.72,0:15:12.09,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,which is better for living and for fields, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.75,0:15:15.68,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Depositional plains, was that their name?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.68,0:15:18.43,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,School classes come in handy...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.21,0:15:33.53,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, Tohya.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.78,0:15:34.83,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.93,0:15:37.79,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you come over here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.97,0:15:39.39,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.04,0:15:44.27,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Dariella... Are you on a morning walk?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.27,0:15:45.15,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.15,0:15:47.05,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a light sleeper.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.35,0:15:49.31,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,You live in Minami, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.31,0:15:51.18,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I travel all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.47,0:15:55.47,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,My job is to go all around, \Nand write down what I see and hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.89,0:16:00.31,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,But I suppose my home would be near Ikoma.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.31,0:16:01.06,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Ikoma?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.52,0:16:04.94,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Past Kyoto, is how I think you would describe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.40,0:16:06.62,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.62,0:16:09.74,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,But I live alone in a shack.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.74,0:16:12.52,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't a place where you get visitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.86,0:16:15.57,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,So when I want to enjoy the town air,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.57,0:16:17.08,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I go on journeys like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.57,0:16:18.95,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that dangerous?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.95,0:16:20.64,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I'm used to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.64,0:16:26.59,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,And the roads have gotten a lot safer \Nsince Plant Hwyaden started patrolling.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.10,0:16:29.05,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Plant Hwyaden, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.52,0:16:51.65,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Plant Hwyaden has made Minami into \Na beautiful, prosperous town.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.65,0:16:53.86,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Have you no interest in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.13,0:16:55.98,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.98,0:17:00.59,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Then, if you get the chance, come to my house.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.03,0:17:04.62,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,If you do, I'll show you around.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.62,0:17:06.72,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,We'll go out together.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.25,0:17:10.92,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,You've been avoiding looking at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.92,0:17:12.32,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.05,0:17:16.27,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,You don't dislike me, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.27,0:17:17.94,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,That part of you, I do dislike!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.52,0:17:22.30,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,You're always smiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.30,0:17:23.31,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.18,0:17:26.40,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,What of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.90,0:17:29.77,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,You wouldn't look weird without that smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.85,0:17:33.15,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,You'd look better that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.92,0:17:35.94,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,That isn't true.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.50,0:17:39.91,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.73,0:17:47.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.60,0:17:48.85,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,How rude!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.85,0:17:51.46,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Well, where'd you even come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.46,0:17:52.90,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,The window.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.90,0:17:54.97,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,At least come in the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.97,0:17:55.88,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.88,0:17:59.00,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,The reconnaissance went off without a hitch.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.00,0:18:01.45,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,There wasn't any problem this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.45,0:18:03.35,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Well, we were mostly after basic information.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.05,0:18:05.85,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Can I report to you now?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.85,0:18:07.60,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.97,0:18:10.85,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Regarding the city of Maihama \Nand the Cowen family,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.85,0:18:16.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you're well acquainted with Princess \NLenessia's grandfather, Sergiatte, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.31,0:18:16.86,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.62,0:18:22.37,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Duke Sergiatte's recent favorite \Nfoods are seaweed salad and dorayaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.70,0:18:25.38,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Before bed, he has a glass of warm milk.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.31,0:18:27.84,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.84,0:18:29.55,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know all that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.55,0:18:31.63,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Did you sneak into the castle or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.37,0:18:33.84,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Lenessia told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.84,0:18:34.84,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.28,0:18:37.53,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I got this information using my feminine skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.36,0:18:40.90,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Feminine skills...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.90,0:18:43.75,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Do you doubt my feminine skills?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.75,0:18:45.47,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,No, not really...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.74,0:18:48.38,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,My feminine skills are amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.38,0:18:49.39,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.39,0:18:51.17,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I even went to a girls' night out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.91,0:18:53.73,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.99,0:18:58.07,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,"Well"? I think it's good to have friends...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.44,0:19:00.30,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.30,0:19:01.57,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Then, continuing my report...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.27,0:19:06.79,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,The well-regarded Duke Sergiatte is the Cowen \Nfamily head and is sixty years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.79,0:19:09.20,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,His wife has already passed away.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.20,0:19:12.34,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,When he was young, he led the \Nknights against monsters...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.02,0:19:14.56,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, my lord?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.16,0:19:17.40,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You look unhappy, as usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.40,0:19:19.93,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, well. You see...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.61,0:19:23.13,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Reports from the chief have stopped coming in.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.13,0:19:24.51,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,From the old master?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.51,0:19:25.95,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,That's rare.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.95,0:19:27.89,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,He isn't responding to telepathy, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.40,0:19:30.32,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Is that possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.32,0:19:31.90,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,No, not normally.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.61,0:19:36.25,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,It makes me a little worried \Nabout Minori and the gang.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.42,0:19:39.56,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,He isn't picking up on telepathy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.56,0:19:40.36,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.36,0:19:42.79,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to talk to him about something...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.79,0:19:44.27,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,This is strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.27,0:19:45.43,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,When did this start?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.96,0:19:49.37,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.37,0:19:52.20,Default - flashback,N,0000,0000,0000,,And I don't know if it's a side effect of that,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.20,0:19:55.13,Default - flashback,N,0000,0000,0000,,but I'm told it disturbs the voices \Nof adventurers' hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.71,0:19:57.80,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Did she mean telepathy?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.59,0:20:03.10,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,That mobile temple might somehow \Nbe affecting things.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.78,0:20:05.89,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's ask the knights.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.34,0:20:07.77,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,They look a little scary,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.77,0:20:10.96,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,but they're protecting the People of the Land.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.96,0:20:11.89,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.15,0:20:16.08,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,If only Shiroe were here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.91,0:20:19.13,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,That's no good.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.13,0:20:22.24,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,We decided to try to avoid relying on him \Nand the others as much as we could.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.24,0:20:23.74,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.10,0:20:28.75,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,You dislike me, don't you, Tohya?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.75,0:20:30.00,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,No, I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.73,0:20:33.50,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Then why would you say something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.04,0:20:43.11,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.96,0:20:46.42,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, what's Roe 2 going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.42,0:20:48.22,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I wonder, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.22,0:20:50.59,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,She said she was going to Ikoma.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.59,0:20:52.98,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe she'll go with Dariella?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.23,0:20:55.91,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Isuzu won't leave her room, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.00,0:20:58.73,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe something happened with Rudy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.31,0:21:04.93,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,If Roe 2 will be splitting up with us, \Nwe can't rely on her summons.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.93,0:21:08.70,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,We need to find a place to \Nrepair our summon flutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.44,0:21:10.80,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Serara?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.80,0:21:12.49,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.21,0:21:15.50,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like black clouds...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.52,0:21:21.26,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,No, that isn't a cloud.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.07,0:21:26.44,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Those are wyverns!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.19,0:21:29.43,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,They're heading straight for this town!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.68,0:21:31.89,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.80,0:21:36.92,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Hide somewhere safe, Dariella!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.92,0:21:39.19,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,What are you going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.61,0:21:42.78,Default - italics,T,0000,0000,0000,,What the heck is going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.42,0:22:01.96,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Individual levels confirmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.25,0:22:06.47,Monsters,M,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7}Wyvern \NRank/Normal
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.61,0:22:06.47,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,42, 46, 43, 50!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.68,0:22:08.67,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,What do we do, Minori?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.67,0:22:12.45,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Regardless of their levels, \Nwe can't handle that many!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.45,0:22:13.97,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Minori! Serara!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.01,0:22:15.08,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.08,0:22:16.76,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,We have to get out of town for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.76,0:22:18.70,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,We can't let this place become a battlefield!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.70,0:22:19.44,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.44,0:22:20.23,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.23,0:22:21.38,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.38,0:22:22.82,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Serara.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.82,0:22:23.73,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.00,0:24:10.90,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,The Odyssey Knights stand against the \Nwyvern horde attacking the town.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.90,0:24:16.51,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,They fight not to protect, \Nbut to risk their lives in a horrific battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.51,0:24:18.57,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya and the others are frozen stiff.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.57,0:24:20.94,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,But Isuzu and Rudy run...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.29,0:24:23.73,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,To challenge a god to a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.73,0:24:30.94,Title,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,The Red Night
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.19,0:24:25.88,Default,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,Next time: The Red Night.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.19,0:24:28.27,Default,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,I have friends to run with me.
